Preheat the #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Halve the @baby potatoes{500%g} lengthways, quartering any larger pieces.

Pop onto a lined #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Rub the oil over the potatoes then lay them cut-side down on one-half of the baking tray (leaving room for the peppers).

Roast on the top shelf of the oven until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}.

Cut the caps off the @bell pepper{2} and remove the core and seeds (reserve the caps for serving).

To create your Jack O'lanterns, carefully cut out scary faces with a #knife{}.

When the potatoes have been cooking for ~{15%minutes}, place the peppers—open-side up with the caps next to them—on the tray alongside (use two #baking trays{} if necessary).

Return to the oven for remaining time, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> Kids can help to carve the spooky shapes.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Chop the @tomato{2} into 1cm chunks.

Drain the @sweetcorn{1%pack} in a #sieve{}.

Roughly chop the @coriander{5%g} (stalks and all).

In a #bowl{}, combine the corn, tomato and half the coriander. Toss with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}, salt and pepper.

Place a pan over medium-high heat (without oil).

Fry the @Irish beef mince{240%g} and @chorizo{100%g} until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Meat is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add @Central American style spice mix{2%sachets} and garlic. Fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Add @tomato paste{1%tin}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{75%ml}. Cook for ~{2-3%minutes}. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

> Add a splash of water if you feel the mince is too dry.

Remove the peppers and the caps from the oven.

Stuff the peppers with the spiced mince.

Sprinkle the @grated cheese{50%g} on top.

Return to the oven (with caps on the side) until the cheese has melted, another ~{5%minutes}.

> Have the kids help stuff the pepper.

Divide the bell pepper Jack O'lanterns between plates.

Sprinkle with remaining coriander. Place the caps back on top.

Add the salsa and roasted potatoes alongside.

Drizzle half the @creme fraiche{65%g} over the potatoes to create mummy-like strips.

Serve any remaining creme fraiche on the side.